name: MFI Recovery Center Riverside Outpatient Services and Administrative Offices
review_text: They are bery unprofessional and apparently being late for staff is completely normal and if you question them about it watch out youll get reprimanded like a child while they take no accountability for the fact that being late is being late. The employee went as far as saying they have 10 mins grace period, mind you tgis group is daycare and if she is late so am I.... I was under the impression 10 mins grace was for clients not employees. And considering a grace period stands for once in a blue moon not every 3 days in a row like i had experienced. clients are expected to be on time and so are employees.was justifying being tardy to group. i felt so personally hurt. And untrusting for my kids being there even if it is only a half hour. If your looking for honest recover withwith reliable professional staff that respect your time and sensitive situation dont put yourself threw dealing with them. They are taking advantage of people who need help gaslighting them to cover up there own mistakes. Do better mfi. Its really sad the levels of incompetence i experienced in the few days i came here. Im my two years of soder time IV never been so frustrated. I will be filing an incident report with my insurance. Go to ivrs inland valley recovery. They run a tight program that sets you up for success outpaint and in patent .and don't ever take less care than you deserve.

MFI Recovery Center Riverside Outpatient Services and Administrative Offices
review_text: 16 years ago  I  arrived at MFI My  Family  Incorporated,  I was given my life back, I learned to live and not just EXIST,  drug addiction is a vicious cycle,  nobody likes to be addicted, this place gave me the armor and weapons to beat my demons,  ,I  searched for MFI today because my cousin passed away not sure if it's was an overdose,  I  feel sad and for the ones that have not been able to make it out of the never ending cycle of drug abuse. Please if you are reading this and are using,  it's time and MFI  can help you, I'm living proof, if you were to meet me today and I would tell you my past you would not believe me  that I was was a drug addict,  not ashamed because I pulled through  and I am who I am today because of it.

review_text: We tried to work with this treatment center and our experience has been awful. The staff acted aggressively toward us and began spreading false information on social media about our treatment center.  Cyber bullying or smear campaigns on social media are not tolerated in any circumstance and we hope that management will train their employees to conduct self in a professional manner.  This is unacceptable.

name: MFI Recovery Center Riverside Outpatient Services and Administrative Offices
MFI Recovery Center Riverside Outpatient Services and Administrative Offices
review_text:
Even if the amount of stars in this review was infinite, it would not do justice of what I am about to say.

The MFI team saved my life.

I don't believe Google is the appropriate social media outlet for me to get into all of the details of the where's, when's who's and why's of myself... but if you are reading this review, chances are, you or a loved one are facing some extremely difficult times. Please, please, please.... make the next step. Bring yourself, or whoever it is that needs the help, into MFI. Call. Walk in. Do whatever necessary to get the help that could possibly save a life.

The MFI staff are caring, friendly, but most importantly, understanding of the appropriate treatment. Most their have been where we have.
